  "prompt": "What is the limit to follow in Instagram?",
  "response": "As of my last update, Instagram imposes various limits to prevent spam and misuse of the platform. These limits can occasionally change, and they might vary based on an account's activity level and other factors. Generally, here are some common limits:\n\n1. **Following Limit**: You can follow up to 7,500 accounts. Once you hit this limit, you need to unfollow some accounts before you can follow new ones.\n\n2. **Follow/Unfollow Actions**: There's no official number from Instagram, but a commonly suggested limit is around 200 actions per day, combining follows and unfollows. Rapid actions could lead to temporary blocks.\n\n3. **Likes**: You can like up to approximately 1,000 posts per day.\n\n4. **Comments**: The limit is around 200 comments per day, but excessive commenting, especially with similar comments, may lead to action blocks.\n\n5. **Posts**: There's no specific daily limit for posting, but excessive posting might trigger temporary action limits. \n\n6. **Direct Messages (DMs)**: Limits seem to exist around 50 to 100 DMs per day, particularly when reaching out to people who don't follow you back.\n\nThese limits are also influenced by the age of your account, its reputation, and your engagement patterns. Newly created accounts might have stricter limits, while older accounts in good standing might have more leeway. Instagram's algorithms continuously update to reduce spam and improve user experience, so it's best to adhere to community guidelines and avoid automation or spammy activities.",
